Apply UX Writing Ultrawork before final handoff. Read `WRITING.md` first and treat it as the writing contract.

- `WRITING.md` overrides generic UX writing rules.
- Read `TERMS.md` and remove avoid terms from public UI copy.
- Create `.opendock/runs/ux-writing/<run-id>/manifest.md` from `.opendock/templates/ux-writing/WRITING_RUN.md` and list only files created or changed for this task under `Target Files`.
- The harness validates only explicit target files from argv or the active writing run manifest; do not use it as a whole-project scanner.
- Korean copy must follow the configured tone and avoid developer jargon unless allowed by `WRITING.md`.
- English copy must be plain, concise, sentence case, and action-first unless `WRITING.md` says otherwise.
- Error copy must include a useful next action.
- Button/CTA copy should name the user's next action.
- Naming must fit the product concept and avoid internal code names.

Run `node .opendock/harness/opendock__ux-writing-ultrawork/check.mjs` when possible.
